- Dysentery
- Plague
- Yellow fever
- Typhoid fever
- Meningococcal Meningitis
- Measles
- Disease earmarked for eradication and elimination are:
- Leprosy
- Poliomyelitis
- Neonatal tetanus
- Dracunculiosis
- Diseases of public health importance are:
- Malaria
- New AIDS cases
- Tuberculosis
- Childhood pneumonia
- Childhood diarrhea
- STI
- Challenges faced by IDSR in Kenya:
- Linkage to action is weak at lower levels due to lack of capacity for data analysis
- Weak reporting \& communication system from health facilities to county/central surveillance unit
- Weak laboratory capacity \& network
- Lack of quarantine \& adequate isolation facilities
- Insufficient early warning systems for epidemic preparedness $\&$ response
